<div1 type="trialAccount" id="t18360815-2015">
               <interp inst="t18360815-2015" type="uri" value="sessionsPapers/18360815"></interp>
               <interp inst="t18360815-2015" type="date" value="18360815"></interp>
               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18360815-2015-charge-1" targOrder="Y" targets="def1-2015-18360815 t18360815-2015-offence-1 t18360815-2015-verdict-1"></join>
               <p>2015. <persName id="def1-2015-18360815" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-2015-18360815" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2015-18360815" type="age" value="23"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2015-18360815" type="surname" value="MATTHEWS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-2015-18360815" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM MATTHEWS</hi>
                  </persName> was indicted<rs id="t18360815-2015-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18360815-2015-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18360815-2015-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp> for stealing, on the <rs id="t18360815-cd-215" type="crimeDate">
                        <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360815-2015-offence-1 t18360815-cd-215"></join>12th of August</rs>, 12 umbrellas, value 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., the goods of <persName id="t18360815-name-1446" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1446" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1446" type="surname" value="EVANS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1446" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1446" type="occupation" value="wholesale umbrella-manufacturer"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18360815-2015-offence-1 t18360815-name-1446"></join>Thomas Evans</persName>.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1447" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1447" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1447" type="surname" value="BRUCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1447" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>ELIZA BRUCE</persName>
                  </hi>. I am in the employ of Thomas Evans. On the 12th of August, I was taking twelve umbrellas to him, Silver-street, at eight o'clock in the evening—I put them in the passage, where we always put the work, by the warehouse-door, and sat down about half a yard from them—my attention was called by a young woman, and they were gone—I went after a man in white trowsers, who had come into the passage—I spoke to him, and said, "You have got my work"—he said something—I saw the prisoner in Addle-street, and saw him drop my umbrellas—he was running at the time—I hallooed out, "Stop thief"—he was stopped, but not in my presence—the umbrellas were picked up, and given to me—I was about four yards from the prisoner, on the other side of the road, at the time—I saw him again in about ten minutes.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1448" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1448" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1448" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1448" type="given" value="THOMAS FREESTON"></interp>THOMAS FREESTON KIRBY</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Addle-street. On the evening of the 12th of August I saw the prisoner in Addle-street, with a bundle of umbrellas—he was running—I saw him drop them—I heard the prosecutrix cry, "Stop thief," and ran after him till he was taken, by a person, at the end of Philip-lane, and given to an officer—he had run about two hundred yards after dropping them, and turned a corner—I was so close to him, and did not lose sight of him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you keep sight of him all the time? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> Yes—the person who took him is not here—he was given into the custody of an officer—I was about thirty yards from him when he</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183608150190"></xptr>
               <p>was stopped—the moment he dropped the umbrellas, he ran away so fast it was almost impossible any body could run so swift—the corner is not twenty yards from where he dropped the umbrellas—he had dark trowsers on—I had never seen him before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1449" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1449" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1449" type="surname" value="EARL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1449" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>FRANCIS EARL</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a constable of Cripplegate. I heard the cry of "Stop thief" and saw the prisoner running down Phillip-lane—I endea<lb></lb>voured to stop him, but missed my hold—I turned round and pursued him—another person, a stranger, caught hold of him—I came up almost imme<lb></lb>diately and secured him—Kirby came to the station-house directly after<lb></lb>wards—I did not notice him before.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> He did not come up where the prisoner was stop<lb></lb>ped? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did notice—him—there were a great many people there.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1450" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1450" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1450" type="surname" value="EVAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1450" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS EVAN</persName>
                  </hi>. I am the employer of Bruce—the umbrellas are mine. <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> What are you? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> A wholesale umbrella-manu<lb></lb>facturer—these are not finished, but they are complete enough to answer the purpose of umbrellas.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was returning from my master's—I went to my mother's and on coming back, I was going to Billingsgate to assist my wife home, and on the road in Wood-street I heard a cry of "Stop thief"—I ran with the other people—a man in white trowsers was running, and that man let the bundle fall out of his arm—I turned one way, and suppose the man went the other—as soon as I turned the corner I was laid hold of—four or five people came to the station-house, and said I was not the man who dropped it, that it was a person in white trowsers; but they were all pushed away from the door—the door was shut in their faces—they pro<lb></lb>mised to come forward, but I do not know whether they are here.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1451" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1451" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1451" type="surname" value="FORD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1451" type="given" value="MARY ANN"></interp>MARY ANN FORD</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Phillip-lane, my husband works in Al<lb></lb>dersgate-street. I was in Silver-street on the 12th of August, and as I came across from Silver-street, there was a young man with a bundle of umbrellas under his left arm—they were covered with green baize—the young man came across the road, and his right arm touched my left—an umbrella-maker living in our court, made me take notice, and I followed him down opposite the locksmith's—the people came running down the street—he turned his head, saw them running, and threw down the umbrellas in the gutter, a few yards from me—I did not go to the watch-house when the prisoner was taken—I do not know him—the man had dirty looking white trowsers on—the prisoner is not the young man I saw throw down the umbrellas—I cannot say it was not him—I saw no features because I was behind him, but I am sure he had dirty looking white trowsers—when they were thrown down there was a cry of "Stop thief"—there were several persons standing who might have taken him, but I could not see his face.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1452" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1452" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1452" type="surname" value="BOLTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1452" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES BOLTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am an appraiser, and live in Addle-street. On the 12th of August, I was returning home from Aldermanbury—I had arrived near the end of Phillip-lane, when I heard the cry of "Stop thief", and immediately afterwards saw two men run past me, one in white trowsers, and the other in dark—the one in white trowsers was on the right hand side, and the other on the left—I turned after them, and went down to the end of the street—they then parted, the man in white trowsers to the right, and the other to the left—two girls were following them—I returned towards my own home, and when I got to Philip-lane, I found somebody in custody—I then went to the station-house, and was refused admission—I really cannot say whether the prisoner was either of those men.</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183608150191"></xptr>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1453" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1453" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1453" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1453" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS KIRBY</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined</hi> There were two men running—one in white trowsers, and the prisoner in dark trowsers—I stopped the man in white trowers because he was nearest to me—he said, "It is not me," and I saw the prisoner with the bundle under his arm—I let the man in white trowsers go—and followed the prisoner and saw him drop the bundle.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PHILLIPS</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Why not tell his Lordship in the first instance that you stopped the man in white trowsers? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> The question was not put to me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1454" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1454" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1454" type="surname" value="BOLTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1454" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BOLTON</persName>
                  </hi>. No one was passing, no one pursued or stopped the man in white trowsers I solemnly declare—nobody could stop from the end of Phillip-lane to Aldermanbury.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1455" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1455" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1455" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1455" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS KIRBY</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> It was in Addle-street I stopped him—the man who dropped the umbrellas was not twenty yards from me at the time—I did not lose sight of him till he was taken—the other took the right hand side, and this man the left, and I took him—he is the man who was taken to the station-house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1456" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1456" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1456" type="surname" value="BRUCE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1456" type="given" value="ELIZA"></interp>ELIZA BRUCE</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I saw the prisoner drop the umbrella—I did not see the face, but he is the person—I spoke to the man with white trowsers and said, "You have got my work," he said, "No; it is not me, I have not got your work"—so I turned my head, and saw this man running with them—the man in white trowsers came into the passage, and I thought it was him at first, and followed, and spoke to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360815-name-1457" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1457" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1457" type="surname" value="KIRBY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-name-1457" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS KIRBY</persName>
                  </hi>. He dropped the umbrellas before he turned the corner—that was the time he gained ground on me—I positively did not lose sight of him—I saw the prisoner at the station-house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">
                     <rs id="t18360815-2015-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
                        <interp inst="t18360815-2015-verdict-1" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360815-2015-verdict-1" type="verdictSubcategory" value="no_subcategory"></interp>GUILTY</rs>
                  </hi>. Aged 23.—
